@ritamcj any update on using the ElementJacobianDamper
How is the time step decreasing? Is this just the IterationAdaptiveDT decreasing it?
You should play with the parameters of this time stepper. If the system never becomes 'easy' to solve, then it will continuously cut the time step.

@abarun22 do you actually need to specify the reset_apps parameter? This parameter is only used to restrict the apps that are being reset. So within a MultiApp with 4 subapps for example, only reset apps 1 and 3 with 'reset_apps = 1 3'
Very often though, all subapps should be reset in which case this parameter need not be specified.
wrt diagnosing the issue. It seems the reset sets up a 'sequence' output. You can achieve similar output with that parameter of the Exodus output.
